<exercise checkit-seed="0000" checkit-slug="SQ1" checkit-title="Sequence formulas">
    <statement>
        <ol>
            <li>
                Find the first 5 terms of the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>a_n=-2 \, n + 1.</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find a closed form for the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>5, \frac{5}{4}, \frac{5}{16}, \frac{5}{64}, \frac{5}{256},\ldots</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            <li>
                Find a recursive form for the following sequence:
                <ul>
                    <li><m>3, 4, 7, 12, 19,\ldots</m></li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            
        </ol>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <ol>
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li><m>-1, -3, -5, -7, -9</m> if you start with <m> n=1</m>, or <m>1, -1, -3, -5, -7</m> if you start with <m> n=0</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Answers can vary depending on your choice of starting index.  For example, <m>5 \, \left(\frac{1}{4}\right)^{n}</m> if <m> n=0,1,...</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
            <li>
                <ul>
                    <li>Answers can vary depending on your choice of starting index.  For example, if <m>a_0=3</m> then <m>a_n=1a_{n-1}+2 \, n - 1</m>.</li>
                    ,
                </ul>
            </li>
            
           
        </ol>
    </answer>
</exercise>
